    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 225ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-harissa-lean-pork-chilli-with-lime-pickled-onion/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>mince</strong> (remove the paper if required!) and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-harissa-lean-pork-chilli-with-lime-pickled-onion/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely slice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>lime[s] </strong>into wedges</p><p>Add 1/4 of the <strong>sliced red onion</strong> to a small bowl (you'll use the rest later!) with 4 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[6 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [8 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-purple\"> </span><strong>boiled water</strong>, the juice of <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lime wedges</strong> (not sure about citrus? Try using less!) a pinch of <strong>sugar </strong>and <strong>salt</strong> and set aside to pickle \u2013 this is your <strong>lime pickled onion</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-harissa-lean-pork-chilli-with-lime-pickled-onion/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pork is beginning to brown, add the <strong>remaining sliced red onion</strong> to the pan and cook for a further 3-4 min or until softening</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-harissa-lean-pork-chilli-with-lime-pickled-onion/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain and rinse your <strong>black beans</strong></p><p>Once the onion is softening, reduce the heat to medium-high, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and your <strong>smoked ground paprika</strong> to the pan<strong> </strong>and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-harissa-lean-pork-chilli-with-lime-pickled-onion/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong> to the pan with the <strong>drained black beans</strong>, your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong>, 1/2 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3/4 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[170ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 3-4 min or until thickened</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-harissa-lean-pork-chilli-with-lime-pickled-onion/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once thickened, add your <strong>harissa paste</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and stir it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>smoky harissa lean pork chilli</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-harissa-lean-pork-chilli-with-lime-pickled-onion/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain the <strong>lime pickled onion</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>smoky harissa lean pork chilli</strong> over the <strong>cooked rice</strong></p><p>Drizzle over your <strong>natural yoghurt</strong>, sprinkle with your <strong>smoked sea salt flakes</strong> and top with the <strong>lime pickled onion</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
